headline: Game On: Take-Two reports mixed Q4 earnings results
summary: “Game On” is The Fly’s weekly recap of the stories powering up or beating down video game stocks. TAKE-TWO REPORTS MIXED Q4 EARNINGS RESULTS: Last week, Take-Two (TTWO) reported a fourth quarter loss per share of ($21.08) on net bookings of $1.58B, which compared to a loss per share of ($17.02) for the same period last year and analyst net bookings estimates of $1.55B. headline: Traders Brace for Treasury 10-Year Yield at 5% as Mood Sours
summary: (Bloomberg) -- Traders are piling into bets that long-term Treasury yields will surge on concerns over the US government’s swelling debt and deficits, a situation made more precarious by President Donald Trump’s tax-cut bill.
